# Gobuster Basics

## What is Gobuster

Gobuster is a fast directory, file, DNS subdomain, and virtual host brute-forcing tool written in Go. It is one of the most commonly used enumeration tools in CTFs and real penetration tests.

---

## Installation

```bash
# Kali Linux / Parrot OS — already installed
gobuster --help

# Manual install
sudo apt install gobuster

# From source
go install github.com/OJ/gobuster/v3@latest
```

---

## Modes

| Mode | What it does |
|------|-------------|
| `dir` | Brute force directories and files |
| `dns` | Brute force DNS subdomains |
| `vhost` | Brute force virtual hosts |
| `fuzz` | Fuzz any part of a URL |
| `s3` | Enumerate Amazon S3 buckets |

---

## Dir Mode — Directory and File Brute Forcing

Find hidden directories and files on a web server.

```bash
gobuster dir -u http://target.com -w /usr/share/wordlists/dirb/common.txt
```

### Common flags

| Flag | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| `-u` | Target URL |
| `-w` | Wordlist path |
| `-x` | File extensions to append |
| `-t` | Number of threads (default 10) |
| `-o` | Output file |
| `-b` | Status codes to blacklist |
| `-s` | Status codes to whitelist |
| `--timeout` | HTTP timeout per request |
| `-k` | Skip TLS certificate verification |
| `-H` | Add a custom HTTP header |
| `-c` | Add cookies |

### Find files with extensions

```bash
gobuster dir \
  -u http://target.com \
  -w /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/common.txt \
  -x php,html,txt,bak,zip \
  -t 50
```

### Authenticated scan (with cookie)

```bash
gobuster dir \
  -u http://target.com \
  -w /usr/share/seclists/Discovery/Web-Content/common.txt \
  -c "session=abc123"
```

### HTTPS with self-signed cert

```bash
gobuster dir -u https://target.com -w wordlist.txt -k
```

