## Reading Output
/admin                (Status: 301) [Size: 312] [--> http://target.com/admin/]

/login                (Status: 200) [Size: 1542]

/backup               (Status: 403) [Size: 287]

/.htaccess            (Status: 403) [Size: 287]

/config.php           (Status: 200) [Size: 0]

| Status | Meaning |
|--------|---------|
| 200 | Found and accessible |
| 301/302 | Redirect — follow it |
| 403 | Forbidden — exists but blocked |
| 404 | Not found |
| 500 | Server error — may indicate it exists |

A 403 is still interesting — it means the directory exists even if you cannot access it directly.

---

## CTF Tips

- Always try `-x php,txt,html,bak,zip,old,conf` for file extensions
- 403 pages sometimes bypass with path tricks: `/admin/`, `/admin//`, `/%2fadmin/`
- Use `raft-large-files.txt` to find backup and config files like `config.bak`, `db.sql`, `.env`
- Try both `/` and no trailing slash

